    "# Credit Card Fraud Detection — Feature Engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "In the previous project, machine learning models were built to classify fraudulent transactions.  \n",
    "This project focuses on the next important step in the machine learning workflow:\n",
    "\n",
    "> **feature engineering**\n",
    "\n",
    "Feature engineering means creating better input variables from the existing data so that models can learn more useful fraud patterns.\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of changing the entire modeling approach, this notebook improves the **quality of the features** given to the model.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Objectives\n",
    "\n",
    "The main goals of this notebook are to:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. prepare the fraud dataset for feature engineering\n",
    "2. create meaningful new features from existing variables\n",
    "3. train a baseline Random Forest model\n",
    "4. train a feature-engineered Random Forest model\n",
    "5. compare both models using fraud-aware metrics\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Why Feature Engineering Matters\n",
    "\n",
    "Machine learning models are only as good as the data they receive.\n",
    "\n",
    "Raw columns often do not fully capture suspicious behavior, but engineered features can reveal:\n",
    "\n",
    "- unusual transaction timing\n",
    "- unusually large transaction amounts\n",
    "- geographic anomalies\n",
    "- behavior patterns linked to fraud\n",
    "\n",
    "This makes feature engineering one of the most valuable steps in any real-world machine learning project."
   ]
  },
