    "\n",
    "Five new features were successfully created to capture deeper fraud-related patterns:\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 1. Distance (`distance`)\n",
    "Represents the geographic distance between the customer and the merchant.\n",
    "\n",
    "From the preview:\n",
    "- values range around **0.27 to 0.97** in the sample\n",
    "\n",
    "This helps detect transactions occurring far from a customer’s usual location.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2. Night Transaction (`is_night`)\n",
    "Flags transactions between **10 PM and 4 AM**.\n",
    "\n",
    "From the sample:\n",
    "- all displayed transactions have `is_night = 1`, confirming they occurred during late hours\n",
    "\n",
    "Fraud is more likely during unusual hours when monitoring is lower.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 3. Weekend Transaction (`is_weekend`)\n",
    "Flags transactions occurring on weekends.\n",
    "\n",
    "From the sample:\n",
    "- all values are `0`, indicating weekday transactions\n",
    "\n",
    "This helps distinguish behavioral differences between weekdays and weekends.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 4. High Amount Flag (`high_amount_flag`)\n",
    "Identifies transactions above the **95th percentile**.\n",
    "\n",
    "From the sample:\n",
    "- some transactions are flagged as `1`, confirming high-value transactions are being detected\n",
    "\n",
    "Fraud often involves unusually large transaction amounts.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 5. Log-Transformed Amount (`amt_log`)\n",
    "Applies a log transformation to reduce skew in transaction amounts.\n",
    "\n",
    "From the sample:\n",
    "- values are more evenly distributed compared to raw amounts\n",
    "\n",
    "This helps the model handle extreme values more effectively.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Insight\n",
    "\n",
    "These engineered features transform raw data into **behavior-driven signals**:\n",
    "\n",
    "- distance → geographic anomaly  \n",
    "- time → behavioral anomaly  \n",
    "- amount → financial anomaly  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why this matters\n",
    "\n",
    "Unlike basic features, these variables:\n",
    "\n",
    "- highlight suspicious patterns more clearly  \n",
    "- improve the model’s ability to detect rare fraud cases  \n",
    "- provide richer information than raw columns alone  \n",
    "\n",
    "This is where the model starts learning **how fraud actually behaves**, not just what the data looks like."
   ]
